<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I'm not 100% sure that this is a bug, or whether or not I'm using locales inappropriately, however by relying on the en_GB locale and allowing everything to hook into that, such as Zend_Date, ZendX_JQuery, etc. is yielding unexpected results when converting the date format.</p>

<p>The date format for en_GB long and medium is "d MMM y", which when converted from the user input to ISO gets you an unexpected result.</p>

<p>For example - 
User input is "1 Jan 10", which is validated by ZF
When converted to ISO format this yields 0010-01-01.. etc.</p>

<p>Whilst I totally understand why, it would seem more appropriate for the dateformat for long and short to be "d MMM yyyy" by default.</p>

