        <div class="body">
            <p>The dateformat for long in en_GB is: d MMMM y
Whilst the medium format is d MMM y</p>

<p>These are not equal.
What you are refering to is full which is: EEEE, d MMMM y</p>

<p>Note that you here directly within the internals.
These are provided by unicode and not by Zend and they are worldwide agreed. When there is a problem with those data you should open a issue within unicode itself (<a href="http://unicode.org/cldr">http://unicode.org/cldr</a>)</p>

<p>When you need to format/change/work with dates you should use Zend_Date which allows you to change/define your own format.</p>

<p>Zend_Locale itself does NOT provide date methematics. It is also not able to convert dates to ISO.</p>

